Acts like a normal switch case, ngSwitchCase is property binded and each case acts as a structural attirbute with *
Syntax:

<div [ngSwitchCase]="tab"> //tab is a property which defines current tab
    <div *ngSwitchDefault="'Mobiles'">  //Default case that gets executed on page load
    </div>
    <div *ngSwitchCase="'Tablets'">
    </div>
    <div *ngSwitchCase="'Laptops'">
    </div>
    <div *ngSwitchCase="'Computer'">
    </div>
</div>